{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "With the development of the Internet and information technology, data have emerged in massive quantities in the form of networks, covering a wide range of fields such as social networks (Zhang et al. 2022; He et al. 2020; Li et al. 2017; Alvarez-Rodriguez et al. 2021; Tong et al. 2020), citation networks (Tang et al. 2023; Healy et al. 2022; Sarkar and Maiti 2020), molecular networks (Nothias et al. 2020; Aron et al. 2020; Liu et al. 2020; Mokaya et al. 2023), transportation networks (Jana et al. 2303; Jin et al. 2023a; Jiang and Luo 2022), and communication networks (Ju et al. 2024; Suárez-Varela et al. 2022; Jiang 2022; Zhaohui et al. 2021; Cao et al. 2018).",
    "These network data are not only rich in information but also have complex relationships, which provide an opportunity to reveal the intrinsic laws of data.",
    "To effectively mine and utilize this information, graph representation learning has emerged.",
    "It transforms graph structures and features into low-dimensional vectors, making graph data easier to process and analyze for better application in downstream tasks such as graph classification (Xie et al. 2020; Zeng and Xie 2021; Gao and Ji 2019a; Nouranizadeh et al. 2107; Nguyen et al. 2022a; Gutteridge et al. 2023a; He et al. 2023b; Glickman and Yahav 2023; Choi et al. 2402), node classification (Wang et al. 2018; Izadi et al. 2020; Casanova et al. 2018; Abu-El-Haija et al. 2020; Ma et al. 2019a; Kipf and Welling 1609; Hamilton et al. 2017; Xu et al. 1810; Chen et al. 2020a), and link prediction (Glickman and Yahav 2023; Hamilton 2020; Chen et al. 2020b; Rampášek et al. 2022; Wittmann et al. 2024).",
    "As representative methods for graph representation learning, Graph neural networks (GNNs) stand out in the industry for their excellent performance."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
